	// INSERT
	// DELETE
	// EXECUTE
	// RECEIVE
	// REFERENCES
	// The general form for defining an action to be audited is:
	// {action} ON {object} BY {principal}
	// Note that <object> in the above format can refer to an object like a table, view, or stored procedure, or an entire database
	// or schema. For the latter cases, the forms DATABASE::{db_name} and SCHEMA::{schema_name} are used, respectively.
	// For example:
	// SELECT on dbo.myTable by public
	// SELECT on DATABASE::myDatabase by public
	// SELECT on SCHEMA::mySchema by public
